data.description: Welcome to the sought after neighborhood of Norman Downes just minutes from Downtown Duluth. This home sits on a manicured lot with added entertainment space on the lighted patio out back and its own basketball court on the side yard. A lovely Brick front home with all new paint inside, new Hardie plank siding, new roof, newer gutters and garage doors, newer outside paint and more. You are welcomed into the home with a lovely foyer flanked by a large living room and dining room. The cozy family room with fireplace opens out to the patio and fenced backyard. Flowers will be back in the Spring! The kitchen has all stainless steel appliances that also include a refrigerator, granite countertops and it opens up to a large breakfast area. The laundry room off the kitchen also includes a newer washer and dryer. Ready to move in without buying appliances!! Upstairs you have a large primary ensuite that includes a bonus room that could be used as an office, nursery or turned into an amazing closet. There are 3 other spacious bedrooms and a bathroom. This home sits on a lot that is just a quick walk to the neighborhood pool, so no loading up the car to go for a swim. Also down that street next to the tennis courts there is access to the lake for a fishing boat, canoeing and more. Norman Downes is just minutes to Downtown Duluth which offers dining, shopping, festivals, live music venue, playground, and so much more! Also you can walk to Bunten Road Park and Mason Elementary. Minutes from I-85 and PIB.
